- Via arguments to the JVM:

        java -jar anApp.jar -Duser.language=pt-BR

But, just as reference, I want to note that, on Windows, there is one more way of changing the locale used by the JRE, as documented [here](https://www.java.com/en/download/help/locale.xml): changing the system-wide language.

