&gt; _&quot;... Is is possible to set a range for Integers in a Java class? ...&quot;_

No, it is not part of the syntax.

Utilize a _[class structure](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/classes.html)_.

```java
abstract class RangedInt {
    int a, b, value;

    RangedInt(int a, int b, int value) {
        if (value &lt; a || value &gt; b)
            throw new ValueOutOfBounds();
        this.a = a;
        this.b = b;
        this.value = value;
    }

    static class ValueOutOfBounds extends RuntimeException {
    }
}

class Year extends RangedInt {
    Year(int value) {
        super(1900, 2100, value);
    }
}

class Month extends RangedInt {
    Month(int value) {
        super(1, 12, value);
    }
}

class Day extends RangedInt {
    Day(int value) {
        super(1, 31, value);
    }
}
```

